    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cooling the Sidewalk</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Danielle Remp letter on Aug 8 editorial questions why New York City stores run air-conditioners full blast, with doors wide open, at time of energy shortage</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Those Shocking Electric Bills'' (editorial, Aug. 8):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Those Shocking Electric Bills'' (editorial, Aug. 8):</p>
        <p>With an energy shortage in New York, why is there no law prohibiting retail establishments from running their air-conditioners full blast, with their doors wide open?</p>
        <p>DANIELLE REMP  New York, Aug. 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
